{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775838435228,"sessionID":"ses_287ca279cffe3fzcCE8xiTi9ES","part":{"id":"prt_d7838119d001emB1JnDRRqRj9j","messageID":"msg_d783806d3001XvWgWXCa4XqJB9","sessionID":"ses_287ca279cffe3fzcCE8xiTi9ES","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_2320f878320540ad869be8ee","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-015"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-015</path>\n<type>directory</type>\n<entries>\ndesign.md\nproposal.md\ntasks.md\n\n(3 entries)\n</entries>","metadata":{"preview":"design.md\nproposal.md\ntasks.md","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-015","time":{"start":1775838435224,"end":1775838435227}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775838435821,"sessionID":"ses_287ca279cffe3fzcCE8xiTi9ES","part":{"id":"prt_d783818150012dOpthzUSKbTOH","messageID":"msg_d783806d3001XvWgWXCa4XqJB9","sessionID":"ses_287ca279cffe3fzcCE8xiTi9ES","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_14e27a08117145059a7a1068","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/code-execution/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/code-execution/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Code Execution (PicoD) Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: PicoD is an HTTP daemon that runs commands inside a configurable workspace jail, manages workspace files, and exposes a health endpoint with JWT (RSA)–protected APIs.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Requirement: Command execution API\n10: \n11: The system SHALL accept `POST /api/execute` with a JSON body, run `command[0]` with `command[1:]` as arguments via `exec.CommandContext`, capture stdout and stderr into buffers, and respond with HTTP 200 and an `ExecuteResponse` for successful request handling (including non-zero command exit). The request SHALL NOT accept stdin from the client; the process stdin is not set from the request body.\n12: \n13: #### Scenario: Valid execution with defaults\n14: \n15: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT and JSON body with non-empty `command` and empty `timeout`\n16: - **WHEN** the client calls `POST /api/execute`\n17: - **THEN** the server uses a default timeout of 60 seconds, runs the command, and returns `stdout`, `stderr`, `exit_code`, `duration` (seconds), `start_time`, and `end_time` as JSON\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Custom timeout\n20: \n21: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT and JSON body where `timeout` is a non-empty string parseable by Go `time.ParseDuration` (e.g. `\"30s\"`, `\"500ms\"`)\n22: - **WHEN** the client calls `POST /api/execute`\n23: - **THEN** the server uses that duration for the command context timeout\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Timeout exceeded\n26: \n27: - **GIVEN** execution exceeds the context deadline\n28: - **WHEN** the context is cancelled\n29: - **THEN** the response `exit_code` SHALL be `124` (`TimeoutExitCode`) and stderr SHALL include a message that the command timed out with the timeout length in seconds (integer formatting)\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Invalid timeout\n32: \n33: - **GIVEN** `timeout` is non-empty and not a valid duration\n34: - **WHEN** the client calls `POST /api/execute`\n35: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with JSON `error` describing invalid timeout format and `code` 400\n36: \n37: #### Scenario: Empty command\n38: \n39: - **GIVEN** JSON binds successfully but `command` has length zero\n40: - **WHEN** the client calls `POST /api/execute`\n41: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with `error` `\"command cannot be empty\"` and `code` 400\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Working directory inside workspace\n44: \n45: - **GIVEN** `working_dir` is non-empty\n46: - **WHEN** the server resolves it with the same path-safety rules as file APIs\n47: - **THEN** `cmd.Dir` is set to the sanitized absolute path; if resolution fails, the server responds HTTP 400 with `error` prefixed by `\"Invalid working directory: \"`\n48: \n49: #### Scenario: Environment augmentation\n50: \n51: - **GIVEN** `env` is non-empty\n52: - **WHEN** the command runs\n53: - **THEN** `cmd.Env` is the current process environment plus additional entries `key=value` for each map entry\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: Malformed JSON\n56: \n57: - **GIVEN** the body is not valid JSON for `ExecuteRequest`\n58: - **WHEN** binding fails\n59: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with `error` from the binder and `code` 400\n60: \n61: ### Requirement: File upload API\n62: \n63: The system SHALL accept `POST /api/files`. If `Content-Type` starts with `multipart/form-data`, the server SHALL treat the request as multipart upload; otherwise it SHALL bind JSON for `UploadFileRequest`.\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: Multipart upload\n66: \n67: - **GIVEN** `Content-Type` has prefix `multipart/form-data`, form field `path` is set, and form file `file` is present\n68: - **WHEN** the client posts to `POST /api/files`\n69: - **THEN** the server creates parent directories with mode `0755`, writes the uploaded stream to a sanitized path, applies mode from form field `mode` via `parseFileMode` (default `0644` when empty/invalid/exceeds max), and responds HTTP 200 with `FileInfo` using `path` as relative to the workspace root\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Multipart missing path or file\n72: \n73: - **GIVEN** multipart request with empty `path` or missing/unreadable `file`\n74: - **WHEN** the handler runs\n75: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with an appropriate `error` and `code` 400\n76: \n77: #### Scenario: JSON Base64 upload\n78: \n79: - **GIVEN** non-multipart request with JSON `path` and `content` (Base64 standard encoding) required\n80: - **WHEN** the client posts to `POST /api/files`\n81: - **THEN** the server decodes content, creates directories, writes the file with `parseFileMode` on `mode`, and responds HTTP 200 with `FileInfo` (relative `path`)\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Invalid Base64\n84: \n85: - **GIVEN** JSON upload with invalid Base64 in `content`\n86: - **WHEN** decoding fails\n87: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with `error` describing invalid base64 and `code` 400\n88: \n89: ### Requirement: File listing API\n90: \n91: The system SHALL accept `GET /api/files?path=...`, require the `path` query parameter, read the directory at the sanitized path, and return JSON `ListFilesResponse`.\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: Successful listing\n94: \n95: - **GIVEN** `path` refers to an existing directory inside the workspace\n96: - **WHEN** the client calls `GET /api/files?path=<dir>`\n97: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 200 with `files` as an array of `FileEntry` objects (`name`, `size`, `modified`, `mode`, `is_dir`), skipping entries where `entry.Info()` fails\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: Missing query parameter\n100: \n101: - **GIVEN** the `path` query parameter is absent or empty\n102: - **WHEN** the client calls `GET /api/files`\n103: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with `error` `\"Missing 'path' query parameter\"` and `code` 400\n104: \n105: #### Scenario: Directory not found\n106: \n107: - **GIVEN** sanitized path does not exist\n108: - **WHEN** `os.ReadDir` fails with not exist\n109: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 404 with `error` `\"Directory not found\"` and `code` 404\n110: \n111: ### Requirement: File download API\n112: \n113: The system SHALL serve file contents at `GET /api/files/*path` for a sanitized file path, set download-oriented headers, and stream the file with `c.File`.\n114: \n115: #### Scenario: Successful download\n116: \n117: - **GIVEN** the wildcard path resolves to a regular file inside the workspace\n118: - **WHEN** the client calls `GET /api/files/<path>`\n119: - **THEN** the server sets `Content-Description` to `File Transfer`, `Content-Transfer-Encoding` to `binary`, `Content-Disposition` to `attachment; filename=\"<basename>\"`, `Content-Type` from `mime.TypeByExtension` or `application/octet-stream`, and returns the file body\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: Path escapes workspace\n122: \n123: - **GIVEN** the requested path fails `sanitizePath`\n124: - **WHEN** the client calls the download endpoint\n125: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with `error` describing access denied / workspace jail\n126: \n127: #### Scenario: Not a file\n128: \n129: - **GIVEN** the path exists but is a directory\n130: - **WHEN** the client downloads\n131: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with `error` `\"Path is a directory, not a file\"` and `code` 400\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: File missing\n134: \n135: - **GIVEN** the path does not exist\n136: - **WHEN** stat fails with not exist\n137: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 404 with `error` `\"File not found\"` and `code` 404\n138: \n139: ### Requirement: Health endpoint\n140: \n141: The system SHALL expose `GET /health` without JWT middleware and respond HTTP 200 with JSON including `status`, `service`, `version`, and `uptime`.\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: Unauthenticated health\n144: \n145: - **GIVEN** no `Authorization` header\n146: - **WHEN** the client calls `GET /health`\n147: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 200 with `status` `\"ok\"`, `service` `\"PicoD\"`, `version` `\"0.0.1\"`, and `uptime` as a string from `time.Since(server start)`\n148: \n149: ### Requirement: JWT authentication for API routes\n150: \n151: The system SHALL register `/api` routes under a Gin group that uses `AuthManager.AuthMiddleware`. The middleware SHALL require header `Authorization: Bearer <token>`, parse the JWT with an RSA public key, and reject non-RSA signing methods. Valid tokens SHALL allow the request to proceed; after validation the request body SHALL be wrapped with `http.MaxBytesReader` limiting size to `MaxBodySize`.\n152: \n153: #### Scenario: Missing or malformed Authorization\n154: \n155: - **GIVEN** missing header, or a header that is not exactly two space-separated parts with first part `Bearer`\n156: - **WHEN** an `/api` route is hit\n157: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 401 with JSON including `error`, `code` 401, and `detail` explaining the failure\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: Invalid or expired JWT\n160: \n161: - **GIVEN** a Bearer token that fails verification (signature, expiry, etc.) with options `WithExpirationRequired`, `WithIssuedAt`, and `WithLeeway(1 minute)`\n162: - **WHEN** the middleware runs\n163: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 401 with `error` `\"Invalid token\"`, `code` 401, and `detail` containing the verification error\n164: \n165: #### Scenario: Public key required at startup\n166: \n167: - **GIVEN** `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` is unset or does not decode to an RSA public key in PEM form\n168: - **WHEN** `NewServer` initializes\n169: - **THEN** the process SHALL log a fatal error and not continue serving (there is no unauthenticated API mode when the key is missing)\n170: \n171: ### Requirement: Server configuration\n172: \n173: The system SHALL read CLI flags `-port` and `-workspace`, build `picod.Config`, and listen on `\":<port>\"`. If `workspace` is empty, the workspace root SHALL be the current working directory (fatal if `os.Getwd` fails). The HTTP server SHALL use `ReadHeaderTimeout` of 10 seconds.\n174: \n175: #### Scenario: Defaults from CLI\n176: \n177: - **GIVEN** `-port` and `-workspace` use program defaults\n178: - **WHEN** the binary starts\n179: - **THEN** `port` defaults to `8080`, `workspace` defaults to empty (resolved to CWD), and Gin runs in `ReleaseMode` with `Logger` and `Recovery` middleware globally\n\n(End of file - total 179 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Code Execution (PicoD) Specification\n\n## Purpose\n\nPicoD is an HTTP daemon that runs commands inside a configurable workspace jail, manages workspace files, and exposes a health endpoint with JWT (RSA)–protected APIs.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Command execution API\n\nThe system SHALL accept `POST /api/execute` with a JSON body, run `command[0]` with `command[1:]` as arguments via `exec.CommandContext`, capture stdout and stderr into buffers, and respond with HTTP 200 and an `ExecuteResponse` for successful request handling (including non-zero command exit). The request SHALL NOT accept stdin from the client; the process stdin is not set from the request body.\n\n#### Scenario: Valid execution with defaults\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid JWT and JSON body with non-empty `command` and empty `timeout`\n- **WHEN** the client calls `POST /api/execute`\n- **THEN** the server uses a default timeout of 60 seconds, runs the command, and returns `stdout`, `stderr`, `exit_code`, `duration` (seconds), `start_time`, and `end_time` as JSON\n\n#### Scenario: Custom timeout\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"specs/code-execution/spec.md","time":{"start":1775838435812,"end":1775838435819}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775838436407,"sessionID":"ses_287ca279cffe3fzcCE8xiTi9ES","part":{"id":"prt_d78381a65001BeNIVn22z0dZbB","messageID":"msg_d783806d3001XvWgWXCa4XqJB9","sessionID":"ses_287ca279cffe3fzcCE8xiTi9ES","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_8412b71eda0f477d850819c3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/code-execution/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/code-execution/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Code Execution (PicoD) — Design (from source)\n2: \n3: Derived from `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod` and `cmd/picod` in `/tmp/agentcube-ref`. Field names, types, tags, and constants match the Go definitions.\n4: \n5: ## Packages and entrypoint\n6: \n7: - **Main**: `cmd/picod/main.go` — parses flags, constructs `picod.Config`, `picod.NewServer(config)`, `server.Run()`.\n8: \n9: ## CLI flags and defaults\n10: \n11: | Flag        | Type   | Default | Usage string |\n12: |------------|--------|---------|--------------|\n13: | `-port`    | `int`  | `8080`  | `Port for the PicoD server to listen on` |\n14: | `-workspace` | `string` | `\"\"` | `Root directory for file operations (default: current working directory)` |\n15: \n16: `klog.InitFlags(nil)` is called so standard klog flags are also registered.\n17: \n18: ## Environment variables\n19: \n20: | Name | Constant | Usage |\n21: |------|----------|--------|\n22: | `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` | `PublicKeyEnvVar` | PEM-encoded PKIX public key (`PUBLIC KEY` block). Loaded in `NewServer` via `AuthManager.LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()`. If empty, invalid PEM, or not `*rsa.PublicKey`, `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv` returns an error and `NewServer` calls `klog.Fatalf` — **no serve without a valid key**. |\n23: \n24: ## Server configuration struct\n25: \n26: ```go\n27: type Config struct {\n28: \tPort      int    `json:\"port\"`\n29: \tWorkspace string `json:\"workspace\"`\n30: }\n31: ```\n32: \n33: ## Internal server fields (`Server`)\n34: \n35: - `engine *gin.Engine`\n36: - `config Config`\n37: - `authManager *AuthManager`\n38: - `startTime time.Time` — set to `time.Now()` in `NewServer`\n39: - `workspaceDir string` — absolute workspace root after `setWorkspace`\n40: \n41: ### Workspace resolution\n42: \n43: - If `config.Workspace != \"\"`: `setWorkspace(config.Workspace)` → `filepath.Abs` when possible, else fallback to provided string.\n44: - Else: `os.Getwd()` (fatal on error).\n45: \n46: ## Constants\n47: \n48: | Name | Value | File | Meaning |\n49: |------|-------|------|---------|\n50: | `TimeoutExitCode` | `124` | `execute.go` | Exit code when context deadline exceeded |\n51: | `MaxBodySize` | `32 << 20` (32 MiB) | `auth.go` | `http.MaxBytesReader` cap applied after successful JWT check |\n52: | `PublicKeyEnvVar` | `\"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"` | `auth.go` | Env var for PEM public key |\n53: | `maxFileMode` | `0777` | `files.go` | `parseFileMode` rejects modes `> 0777` (falls back to `0644`) |\n54: \n55: ### Default timeouts and modes\n56: \n57: - **Execute default timeout** (when `ExecuteRequest.Timeout == \"\"`): `60 * time.Second` (note: struct comment in source says `\"30s\"` but code uses 60s).\n58: - **Directory creation** (`MkdirAll`): `0755`\n59: - **Default file mode** (`parseFileMode` empty/invalid/too large): `0644` (octal parsed with `strconv.ParseUint(modeStr, 8, 32)`)\n60: \n61: ## Request / response structs (exact JSON tags)\n62: \n63: ### Execute\n64: \n65: ```go\n66: type ExecuteRequest struct {\n67: \tCommand    []string          `json:\"command\" binding:\"required\"`\n68: \tTimeout    string            `json:\"timeout\"`\n69: \tWorkingDir string            `json:\"working_dir\"`\n70: \tEnv        map[string]string `json:\"env\"`\n71: }\n72: \n73: type ExecuteResponse struct {\n74: \tStdout    string    `json:\"stdout\"`\n75: \tStderr    string    `json:\"stderr\"`\n76: \tExitCode  int       `json:\"exit_code\"`\n77: \tDuration  float64   `json:\"duration\"`\n78: \tStartTime time.Time `json:\"start_time\"`\n79: \tEndTime   time.Time `json:\"end_time\"`\n80: }\n81: ```\n82: \n83: - **Binding**: `c.ShouldBindJSON(&req)` on `POST /api/execute`.\n84: - **Command**: `exec.CommandContext(ctx, req.Command[0], req.Command[1:]...)`\n85: - **Stdout/Stderr**: `bytes.Buffer` assigned to `cmd.Stdout` and `cmd.Stderr`; no `cmd.Stdin` assignment.\n86: - **Exit code**: If `errors.Is(ctx.Err(), context.DeadlineExceeded)` → `TimeoutExitCode`; else if `cmd.ProcessState != nil` → `ExitCode()`; else `1` and append `err.Error()` to stderr (with newline if stderr non-empty).\n87: \n88: ### Files — upload response / JSON body\n89: \n90: ```go\n91: type FileInfo struct {\n92: \tPath     string    `json:\"path\"`\n93: \tSize     int64     `json:\"size\"`\n94: \tMode     string    `json:\"mode\"`\n95: \tModified time.Time `json:\"modified\"`\n96: }\n97: \n98: type UploadFileRequest struct {\n99: \tPath    string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n100: \tContent string `json:\"content\" binding:\"required\"`\n101: \tMode    string `json:\"mode\"`\n102: }\n103: ```\n104: \n105: - **Multipart**: `Content-Type` prefix `multipart/form-data` → `handleMultipartUpload`.\n106:   - Form: `c.PostForm(\"path\")`, `c.FormFile(\"file\")`, optional `c.PostForm(\"mode\")`.\n107: - **JSON**: `c.ShouldBindJSON` → Base64 decode `req.Content` with `base64.StdEncoding`.\n108: \n109: ### Files — listing\n110: \n111: ```go\n112: type FileEntry struct {\n113: \tName     string    `json:\"name\"`\n114: \tSize     int64     `json:\"size\"`\n115: \tModified time.Time `json:\"modified\"`\n116: \tMode     string    `json:\"mode\"`\n117: \tIsDir    bool      `json:\"is_dir\"`\n118: }\n119: \n120: type ListFilesResponse struct {\n121: \tFiles []FileEntry `json:\"files\"`\n122: }\n123: ```\n124: \n125: - **Query**: `path := c.Query(\"path\")` (required non-empty).\n126: \n127: ## HTTP error JSON shapes (Gin `gin.H`)\n128: \n129: - **Generic** (400/500): `{\"error\": string, \"code\": int}` (`code` is numeric HTTP status).\n130: - **Auth** (401): `{\"error\": string, \"code\": int, \"detail\": string}`.\n131: \n132: ## Gin setup and route registration\n133: \n134: Pattern from `NewServer`:\n135: \n136: 1. `gin.SetMode(gin.ReleaseMode)`\n137: 2. `engine := gin.New()`\n138: 3. Global: `engine.Use(gin.Logger(), gin.Recovery())`\n139: 4. `authManager.LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()` — fatal on error\n140: 5. API group:\n141: \n142: ```go\n143: api := engine.Group(\"/api\")\n144: api.Use(s.authManager.AuthMiddleware())\n145: {\n146: \tapi.POST(\"/execute\", s.ExecuteHandler)\n147: \tapi.POST(\"/files\", s.UploadFileHandler)\n148: \tapi.GET(\"/files\", s.ListFilesHandler)\n149: \tapi.GET(\"/files/*path\", s.DownloadFileHandler)\n150: }\n151: engine.GET(\"/health\", s.HealthCheckHandler)\n152: ```\n153: \n154: - **Download param**: `path := c.Param(\"path\")`; then `strings.TrimPrefix(path, \"/\")` before `sanitizePath`.\n155: \n156: ## Health response\n157: \n158: ```go\n159: c.JSON(http.StatusOK, gin.H{\n160: \t\"status\":  \"ok\",\n161: \t\"service\": \"PicoD\",\n162: \t\"version\": \"0.0.1\",\n163: \t\"uptime\":  time.Since(s.startTime).String(),\n164: })\n165: ```\n166: \n167: ## HTTP server\n168: \n169: ```go\n170: server := &http.Server{\n171: \tAddr:              fmt.Sprintf(\":%d\", s.config.Port),\n172: \tHandler:           s.engine,\n173: \tReadHeaderTimeout: 10 * time.Second,\n174: }\n175: return server.ListenAndServe()\n176: ```\n177: \n178: ## JWT middleware (`AuthManager`)\n179: \n180: ### Types\n181: \n182: ```go\n183: type AuthManager struct {\n184: \tpublicKey *rsa.PublicKey\n185: \tmutex     sync.RWMutex\n186: }\n187: ```\n188: \n189: ### Key loading (`LoadPublicKeyFromEnv`)\n190: \n191: 1. `keyData := os.Getenv(PublicKeyEnvVar)`\n192: 2. If empty → error: `environment variable %s is not set`\n193: 3. `pem.Decode([]byte(keyData))` — nil block → error `failed to decode PEM block`\n194: 4. `x509.ParsePKIXPublicKey(block.Bytes)` — on success assert `*rsa.PublicKey`\n195: \n196: ### `AuthMiddleware` behavior\n197: \n198: 1. `authHeader := c.GetHeader(\"Authorization\")`\n199: 2. If empty → 401 JSON missing header / JWT required detail\n200: 3. `parts := strings.Split(authHeader, \" \")` — require `len(parts) == 2` and `parts[0] == \"Bearer\"` else 401 invalid format (`Use Bearer <token>`)\n201: 4. `tokenString := parts[1]`\n202: 5. `jwt.Parse(tokenString, func(token *jwt.Token) (interface{}, error) { ... }, jwt.WithExpirationRequired(), jwt.WithIssuedAt(), jwt.WithLeeway(time.Minute))`\n203:    - Key func: require `token.Method` is `*jwt.SigningMethodRSA`; return `am.publicKey` (read lock)\n204: 6. If `err != nil || !token.Valid` → 401 `Invalid token` + detail with verification error\n205: 7. `c.Request.Body = http.MaxBytesReader(c.Writer, c.Request.Body, MaxBodySize)`\n206: 8. `c.Next()`\n207: \n208: **Note**: Any RSA signing method instance satisfies the type assert (e.g. RS256 in tests); HS256 is rejected.\n209: \n210: ## Path security (`sanitizePath`)\n211: \n212: Used by upload, list, download, and execute `working_dir`.\n213: \n214: 1. If `s.workspaceDir == \"\"` → error `workspace directory not initialized`\n215: 2. `resolvedWorkspace := filepath.EvalSymlinks(s.workspaceDir)`; on error fall back to `filepath.Abs` or `filepath.Clean`\n216: 3. `resolvedWorkspace = filepath.Clean(resolvedWorkspace)`\n217: 4. `cleanPath := filepath.Clean(p)`; if absolute, strip leading `os.PathSeparator` from path string\n218: 5. `fullPathCandidate := filepath.Clean(filepath.Join(resolvedWorkspace, cleanPath))`\n219: 6. `relPath, relErr := filepath.Rel(resolvedWorkspace, fullPathCandidate)` — error → access denied\n220: 7. If `strings.HasPrefix(relPath, \"..\"+separator)` or `relPath == \"..\"` → access denied\n221: 8. `resolvedFinalPath, err := filepath.EvalSymlinks(fullPathCandidate)`:\n222:    - If success: re-check `filepath.Rel` against `resolvedWorkspace` for `..` escape; pass → return `resolvedFinalPath`\n223:    - If error (e.g. path does not exist): return `fullPathCandidate` (already verified as inside workspace)\n224: \n225: **Upload/list responses** use `filepath.Rel(s.workspaceDir, safePath)` for JSON `path` on uploaded files (not `resolvedWorkspace` symlink expansion — `safePath` is the sanitized target path).\n226: \n227: ## Multipart vs JSON detection\n228: \n229: ```go\n230: contentType := c.ContentType()\n231: if strings.HasPrefix(contentType, \"multipart/form-data\") {\n232: \ts.handleMultipartUpload(c)\n233: } else {\n234: \ts.handleJSONBase64Upload(c)\n235: }\n236: ```\n237: \n238: ## File download headers (exact strings)\n239: \n240: - `Content-Description`: `File Transfer`\n241: - `Content-Transfer-Encoding`: `binary`\n242: - `Content-Disposition`: `fmt.Sprintf(\"attachment; filename=\\\"%s\\\"\", filepath.Base(safePath))`\n243: - `Content-Type`: `mime.TypeByExtension(filepath.Ext(safePath))` or `\"application/octet-stream\"`\n244: \n245: This document is sufficient to reconstruct handlers, routes, structs, and security checks without reading the repo.\n\n(End of file - total 245 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Code Execution (PicoD) — Design (from source)\n\nDerived from `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod` and `cmd/picod` in `/tmp/agentcube-ref`. Field names, types, tags, and constants match the Go definitions.\n\n## Packages and entrypoint\n\n- **Main**: `cmd/picod/main.go` — parses flags, constructs `picod.Config`, `picod.NewServer(config)`, `server.Run()`.\n\n## CLI flags and defaults\n\n| Flag        | Type   | Default | Usage string |\n|------------|--------|---------|--------------|\n| `-port`    | `int`  | `8080`  | `Port for the PicoD server to listen on` |\n| `-workspace` | `string` | `\"\"` | `Root directory for file operations (default: current working directory)` |\n\n`klog.InitFlags(nil)` is called so standard klog flags are also registered.\n\n## Environment variables\n\n| Name | Constant | Usage |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"specs/code-execution/design.md","time":{"start":1775838436397,"end":1775838436405}}}}
